<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05863</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING A SCHOLARSHIP GRANT FOR EVERY FILIPINO FAMILY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to waive the conditions and expand the privileges granted under the " Universal Access to Quality Tertiary Education Act " ( R.A.No.10931) which provides students free tuition and other school fees in state universities and colleges, local universities and colleges and state-run technical vocational institutions.

Proposes that one member of a Filipino Family shall be a recipient of a scholarship grant to an appropriate college course or training for a technical or vocational skills, and shall cover all related expenses.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : " One Family, One Scholar Act of 2019"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>FORTUNO, JOCELYN F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-12-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2020-01-27)</td><td>2. Velasco (000 2020-02-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2020-01-20</td></tr></table>